13/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A team of experts from NATO's Allied Air Forces North Europe headquarters kicked off a four-day assessment of Macedonia on Thursday (12 December). 
At issue, compliance with the individual programme for partnership between NATO and Macedonia.
Also Thursday, police in Skopje detained Bulgarian millionaire Ivan Mironov on an international investigation warrant issued by Interpol. 
He is accused of siphoning more than $80m in unsecured loans while serving as chief executive of the now bankrupt Balkanbank. 
(MIA, Mediapool, BTA - 12/12/02)
